</div>
<div class="comment" id="comment-47747824">
  <div class="comment_head"><a href="/user/nagonago">nagonago</a> 2 days ago</div>
  <div class="comment_text">When I got a Macbook many years ago, I was surprised how often little utility software like this cost money. I was just so used to the abundance of open source and freeware in the Windows&#x2F;Linux world.<p>No judgement either way, I get that developers want to be compensated for their time. I just always found the difference in culture curious. I guess it&#x27;s because if you&#x27;re willing to spend the extra premium for Apple products, you&#x27;re probably also willing to spend a little extra premium on the software too.</div>
  <button class="comment-replies-toggle" onclick="loadReplies(47747824,this)">1 replies</button>
